LAGOS  – The Chairman of the Nigerian Institution of Estate Surveyors and Valuers (NIESV),Lagos State Branch, ESV(Mrs) Olabisi Demola-Alade , has stated that it is an onerous task for women Estate Surveyors and Valuers to combine their roles as wives and mothers and still be at the front in their profession. She dropped this hint, in an address she delivered at the maiden breakfast meeting of the Women Wing of NIESv,Lagos State Branch. According to Demola-Alade, the Theme of the event ‘Female Estate Surveyors and Valuers in Practice’ shows clearly the need to talk about how women Estate Surveyors and Valuers could maintain a balance between the home and career fronts as women. Her words: “Indeed, history is being made once again at “ The Very Branch” today as we have decided to form a common platform for all the women in the Branch to assess our common needs as women professionals in the real estate sector “. She went on: “Suffice to say that as we face the usual competition and hustle and bustle in the same market with the stronger gender, there is no time to lend ourselves a pity”. In her opening remark, the Coordinator of the Women Wing of NIESV,Lagos State Branch,ESV. (Mrs).Rachael Olawunmi Olufowobi said that the Maiden Edition of the Breakfast Lecture Series was put together to bring women Estate Surveyors and Valuers in the state to rub minds with a view to exposing them to the intricacies of the profession. Olufowobi said that the executive of the women wing which was inaugurated on December 1,2021 was poised to bring more women estate surveyors and valuers into its fold by making the series a continuous one. The event had two guest speakers, ESV(Mrs).Foluke Ismail,FNIVS who spoke on ‘Today’s woman ‘Maintaining A Balance Between Home And Career’ and ESV(Mrs.) Bola Nwazomoh who spoke on ‘Challenge And Solutions-A Discussion With Female Estate Surveyors and Valuers In Practice’’.